        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "## Electrode Potential of Cu²⁺/Cu⁰\n\nThe NIST SRD-46 database specialises in **aqueous metal–ligand stability constants** (formation constants, β values, and pKa data) — it does **not** contain electrode potential / reduction potential data.\n\nFor the Cu²⁺/Cu⁰ half-reaction, the standard value comes from well-established electrochemical references:\n\n| Half-reaction | E° (V vs. SHE) | Conditions |\n|---|---|---|\n| Cu²⁺ + 2 e⁻ → Cu⁰ | **+0.342 V** | 25 °C, unit activity (standard state) |",
